<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Incidentally, a point I have made a few times =
about this situation is that hostile takeovers of hedge fund management fir=
ms are rare, in part because hedge fund managers are usually private compan=
ies and in part because of the problem of client retention: The hedge fund=
=E2=80=99s clients presumably like the current manager, so if you take over=
 the company and force her out, the clients might leave too and you=E2=80=
=99ll be left with nothing.</p>
